{"timestamp": "2025-12-02 15:04:03.277080", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission accepted.\n\nSummary of what I submitted\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [] (no single device conclusively identified as failed)\n- root_cause_name:\n  - host_static_blackhole — to represent the intentional/observed isolation of the 20.200.0.0/24 backend network (not advertised/routed off the load_balancer/backend segment).\n  - link_bandwidth_throttling — to represent the intermittent latency/jitter spikes consistent with transient congestion/processing delay on some paths.\n\nIf you want, I can now:\n- Gather targeted traceroutes from the specific source hosts that showed high jitter to the affected destinations to try to localize the congestion point.\n- Fetch interface counters and CPU/memory stats from the intermediate routers (e.g., server_access_router and the 172.16.x interconnect devices) to check for congestion or processing spikes.\n- Check FRR OSPF neighbor and LSDB state to confirm there are no suppressed LSAs for 20.200.0.0/24 and verify intended isolation is implemented as designed.\n\nWhich follow-up would you like me to run?", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2795, "output_tokens": 234, "total_tokens": 3029, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 2688}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
